OL,3,CKelso man says vulnerable people could
OL,4,Cbe cut off by changes to household
OL,5,Cenergy
OL,7,FEnergy UK, the group representing
OL,8,Fenergy companies, says customers who
OL,9,Fhave not upgraded their meters by the
OL,10,F30 June deadline risk having their
OL,11,Fheating and/or hot water left
OL,12,Fconstantly on or off.
OL,14,FAdvice Direct Scotland warns this
OL,15,Fcould leave some people without access
OL,16,Fto their heating and hot water, or
OL,17,Fhaving to pay higher energy bills.
